Spain’s Deputy Finance Minister May Leave Post, El Mundo Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-06-04T09:12:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/spain-s-deputy-finance-minister-may-leave-post-el-mundo-says.html
Spanish Deputy Finance Minister
Carlos Ocana may leave his post to take a position at Funcas,
the research arm of  Spain ’s savings-bank association,  El Mundo 
reported, citing unidentified people close to Ocana.  Ocana is studying an offer to replace Victorio Valle as the
general director of Funcas, the newspaper said.  A spokeswoman for the  Finance Ministry  who declined to be
cited by name declined to comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net  